column3: Can you give a brief overview of your role within your company?
column4: How clear and widely shared is the innovation vision within the organization?
column5: Do you have suggestions on how the innovation vision can be better communicated within the organization?
column6: To what extent does the organization's leadership support and encourage innovation initiatives?
column7: Can you give examples of how leadership has stimulated or hindered innovation in the organization?
column8: How does the organization promote a culture where employees are encouraged to develop and try out new ideas?
column9: What barriers do you or your team experience when developing and implementing new ideas?
column10: To what extent are structured processes in place for developing and implementing new ideas?
column11: What improvements would you like to see in the processes for developing and implementing innovations?
column12: How effectively does the organization use technology to support and enable innovation?
column13: What technological tools or systems do you think are missing to better support innovation?
column14: To what extent does the organization collaborate within teams and departments to stimulate innovation?
column15: How do you think collaboration between teams can be improved to accelerate innovation?
column16: How adequate is the budget reserved for innovation initiatives within the organization?
column17: What type of investments in innovation would make the most difference within the organization?
column18: To what extent are customer needs and feedback taken into account when developing new products or services?
column19: How could the organization better respond to customer feedback to stimulate innovation?
column20: How does the organization deal with risks associated with innovation initiatives?
column21: What risks do you see in the innovation projects within the organization, and how do you think they can be better managed?
column22: How quickly is the organization able to bring new ideas from concept to implementation?
column23: What obstacles do you think slowed down the innovation process within the organization?
